                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.371,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 58243,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in Rompilla versus Beard will be announced by Justice Souter."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.371,
                        "stop": 249.347,
                        "byte_start": 58243,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.371,
                                "stop": 11.999,
                                "byte_start": 58243,
                                "byte_stop": 76737,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 11.999,
                                "stop": 16.218,
                                "byte_start": 76737,
                                "byte_stop": 93560,
                                "text": "The petitioner Ronald Rompilla was convicted of capital murder."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 16.218,
                                "stop": 30.25,
                                "byte_start": 93560,
                                "byte_stop": 149776,
                                "text": "In preparing for the penalty phase at the trial, at which Rompilla might be sentenced to life imprisonment or to death, Rompilla\u2019s counsel sought mitigating evidence from Rompilla from some of his family members and from medical experts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.25,
                                "stop": 39.169,
                                "byte_start": 149776,
                                "byte_stop": 185407,
                                "text": "Those to us has proved unhelpful and in the end, Rompilla\u2019s penalty phase defense relied on residual doubt and a plea for mercy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.169,
                                "stop": 53.883,
                                "byte_start": 185407,
                                "byte_stop": 244234,
                                "text": "The states penalty case as based in part on the record of victim testimony from an earlier trial that had resulted in Rompilla\u2019s conviction for rape, a crime that he had committed under similar circumstances to this one."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.883,
                                "stop": 67.808,
                                "byte_start": 244234,
                                "byte_stop": 299928,
                                "text": "Rompilla was sentenced to death and his conviction and sentence were affirmed on appeal. With new counsel, Rompilla filed for post conviction relief charging that his trial counsel had provided ineffective assistance under the sixth amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.808,
                                "stop": 75.247,
                                "byte_start": 299928,
                                "byte_stop": 329707,
                                "text": "Rompilla\u2019s new lawyers argued that the trial counsel had failed to honor a significant mitigating evidence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.247,
                                "stop": 95.843,
                                "byte_start": 329707,
                                "byte_stop": 412045,
                                "text": "For example, an easily obtainable school and prison record showed that Rompilla was reared in a slum environment by a father who terrorized him regularly and an alcoholic mother who drank heavily during pregnancy and showed that Rompilla himself exhibited signs of schizophrenia."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.843,
                                "stop": 108.181,
                                "byte_start": 412045,
                                "byte_stop": 461469,
                                "text": "The States Courts, however, found the trial counsel had not been deficient in failing to discover this evidence because by interviewing Rompilla, family members and medical experts, they had made sufficient inquiries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.181,
                                "stop": 116.448,
                                "byte_start": 461469,
                                "byte_stop": 494488,
                                "text": "Rompilla then filed for a federal habeas relief which was granted by the District Court but reversed by a divided Third Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.448,
                                "stop": 123.722,
                                "byte_start": 494488,
                                "byte_stop": 523640,
                                "text": "As explained in an opinion filed with the Clerk of Court today, we now reverse the judgment of the Third Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 123.722,
                                "stop": 137.787,
                                "byte_start": 523640,
                                "byte_stop": 579856,
                                "text": "In looking back on counsel\u2019s performance in a case like this, we realize that counsel act in the thick of things without the clarity of hindsight but we can find no objective justification for one of the counsel\u2019s significant decisions here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.787,
                                "stop": 148.254,
                                "byte_start": 579856,
                                "byte_stop": 621756,
                                "text": "Counsel knew well in advance that the prosecution intended to introduce dramatic victim testimony from the prior rape trial in order to obtain the death penalty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.254,
                                "stop": 156.271,
                                "byte_start": 621756,
                                "byte_stop": 653834,
                                "text": "Nonetheless, trial counsel never looked at the prior conviction file even though it was easily available at Rompilla\u2019s trial courthouse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.271,
                                "stop": 170.674,
                                "byte_start": 653834,
                                "byte_stop": 711408,
                                "text": "Without making reasonable efforts to review the file, defense counsel had no way of knowing whether the prosecution would be quoting selectively from the transcript or whether there were circumstances extenuating the behavior described by the victim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 170.674,
                                "stop": 181.649,
                                "byte_start": 711408,
                                "byte_stop": 755294,
                                "text": "The obligation to get the file was particularly pressing here owing to the similarity of the violent prior offense and to Rompilla\u2019s strategy of residual doubt."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.649,
                                "stop": 190.065,
                                "byte_start": 755294,
                                "byte_stop": 788940,
                                "text": "Counsel\u2019s conversations with Rompilla and his family could not reasonably have been expected to substitute for looking at the file itself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 190.065,
                                "stop": 204.784,
                                "byte_start": 788940,
                                "byte_stop": 847872,
                                "text": "It is uncontested that if counsel had looked in the file, they would have found documents showing a range of new mitigating leads including evidence of Rompilla\u2019s unusually abusive home life and his possible mental illness."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 204.784,
                                "stop": 210.639,
                                "byte_start": 847872,
                                "byte_stop": 871278,
                                "text": "This evidence might well have influenced the jury\u2019s assessment of Rompilla culpability."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 210.639,
                                "stop": 222.681,
                                "byte_start": 871278,
                                "byte_stop": 919448,
                                "text": "For these reasons and others given in the opinion, we reverse the judgment of the Third Circuit and require Pennsylvania either to retry the case on penalty or to stipulate to a life sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 222.681,
                                "stop": 249.347,
                                "byte_start": 919448,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice O\u2019Connor has filed a concurring opinion; Justice Kennedy has filed a dissenting opinion in which the Chief Justice, Justice Scalia and Justice Thomas join."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
